 146:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c **** // Data FIFO
 147:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c **** //--------------------------------------------------------------------+
 148:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c **** 
 149:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c **** 
 150:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c **** /* Device Data FIFO scheme
 151:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****   The controller has a single SPRAM of otg_dfifo_depth 32-bit words shared between all FIFOs and op
 152:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****   otg_dfifo_depth = ghwcfg3.dfifo_depth + EP_LOC_CNT. It is split up into:
 153:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c **** 
 154:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****   - EPInfo: for storing DMA address registers (DxEPDMAn), only required when DMA is used.
 155:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****     gdfifocfg.EPINFOBASE and gdfifocfg.GDFIFOCfg must be configured before gahbcfg.dmaen is set.
 156:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****     The number of words needed per endpoint direction depends on the DMA mode used at runtime:
 157:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****       - Buffer DMA mode: 1 word per endpoint direction
 158:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****       - Scatter/Gather DMA mode: 4 words per endpoint direction
 159:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****   - TX FIFO: one fifo for each IN endpoint. Size is dynamic depending on packet size, starting from
 160:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****   - Shared RX FIFO: a shared fifo for all OUT endpoints. Typically, can hold up to 2 packets of the
 161:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c **** 
 162:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****   We allocate TX FIFOs from top to bottom (using a top pointer), this to allow the RX FIFO to grow 
 163:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/portable/synopsys/dwc2/dcd_dwc2.c ****   possible since the free space is located between the RX and TX FIFOs.
